Lab Comments: 2C-B ruled out, substance appears to be an accidental synthesis error.
Warning:
June 2019:  We are working to confirm that this sample contains the same chemical as other Mickey Mouse tablets recently tested in Switzerland, Wales, and the UK.  The identification done for SaferParty identified the substance as 2-bromo-4,5-DMPEA. 

This is thought to be an accidental product from a failed synthesis of 2C-B where the producer used the wrong starting precursor chemical. This substance is not thought to be strongly psychoactive, but we aren't sure of that at all. If anyone has tried one of these, please let us know.

We hope to both confirm the Mass Spectrum for the sample analyzed by DrugsData/DDL is the same as those from the European labs and further have our experts agree with the identification of this unusual substance.
